{{Infobox person |name = Manny Fontenla-Novoa |image = |caption = | birth_name = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1954|5|13|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Galicia (Spain)|Galicia]], Spain |death_date = |death_place = |known_for = |occupation = Businessman |years_active= |title = former CEO of the [[Thomas Cook Group]] |term = 2003 - August 2011 |predecessor = |successor = [[Harriet Green]] |education = |nationality = Spanish | residence = Surrey, England | salary = | net_worth = | spouse = | children = 4 }}
'''Manny Fontenla-Novoa''' (born 13 May 1954)<ref name="Independent">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/manny-fontenlanovoa-the-bloke-from-spain-who-wants-you-to-take-two-weeks-in-torremolinos-469500.html|title=Manny Fontenla-Novoa: The bloke from Spain who wants you to take two weeks in Torremolinos|last=Townsend|first=Abigail|work=[[The Independent]]|date=12 March 2006}}</ref> is a Spanish-British businessman, the former chief executive of [[Thomas Cook Group]] from 2003<ref name="Independent"/> until his resignation in August 2011. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2011/aug/03/thomas-cook-chief-ousted|last=Bowers|first=Simon|title=Thomas Cook chief executive Manny Fontenla-Novoa replaced|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=3 August 2011}}</ref> He is president at Logitravel group since October 2018.<ref>https://www.preferente.com/noticias-de-turismo/manny-fontenla-sustituye-a-ovidio-andres-en-la-presidencia-de-logitravel-281035.html</ref>
== Personal life == Born in Galicia on 13 May 1954, he moved to the United Kingdom at the age of 11.<ref name="Times">{{cite news|url=http://business.timesonline.co.uk/tol/business/industry_sectors/leisure/article1375356.ece|title=Business big shot: Manny Fontenla-Novoa|accessdate=2010-04-21|location=London|work=The Times|first=Dominic|last=Walsh}}</ref>
==Career== Fontenla-Novoa started his career with Thomas Cook in the printing department in 1972 and held a variety of roles until he joined [[International Leisure Group]] in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thomascookgroup.com/AniteNextPage.asp?p=TCGHEMDIRECTORSBIO#40|title=Thomas Cook| accessdate=2010-04-21}}</ref> After International Leisure Group collapsed, Fontenla-Novoa cofounded tour operator Sunworld in 1991. He joined Thomas Cook after their acquisition of Sunworld in 1996, and was its chief executive from 2003 to 2011.<ref name="Independent"/>
Fontenla-Novoa is also a director of [[Iberostar]], a Spanish hotel chain.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/6034552/Thomas-Cook-chief-is-always-in-holiday-mode.html|last=Cave|first=Andrew|title=Thomas Cook chief is always in holiday mode|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|date=15 August 2009}}</ref>
==Personal life== He lives in [[Surrey]] with his wife and four children.{{fact|date=October 2017}}
