{{Infobox person | name = Pearl Esua-Mensah | image= | image_size = | caption = | nationality=[[Ghanaian]] | known_for= | spouse= | website = }} '''Pearl Esua-Mensah''' is the chief executive officer (CEO) for Media General Ltd, a group of media organisations in Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Modern Ghana|title=Media General Premieres Drama Series Sadia|url=https://www.modernghana.com/entertainment/47047/media-general-premieres-drama-series-sadia.html|website=Modern Ghana|publisher=Modern Ghana|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> She was the former deputy managing director for [[UT Bank]] Ghana.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pulse Ghana|title=Pearl Esua- Mensah; the manager UT will never have again|url=http://www.pulse.com.gh/news/business/meet-the-boss-pearl-esua-mensah-the-manager-ut-will-never-have-again-id4231519.html|website=Pulse Ghana|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref> Pearl Esua-Mensah is a member of the executive women network.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Graphic Online|title=Executive Women Network celebrates first anniversary|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/general-news/executive-women-network-celebrates-first-anniversary.html|website=Graphic Online|publisher=Graphic.com.gh|accessdate=31 March 2018}}</ref>
